The paper discusses the optimization of large scale non-smooth non-convex problems, specifically in the context of training sparse deep neural networks and sparse convolutional neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of optimization methods and neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
